  <section class="seasonSection seasonIntro">
    <h2>Concise strategic guide for the alliance</h2>
    <p>Season 6, <b>Shadow Rainforest</b>, changes the game from a normal growth or single-server war phase. The key is not only individual power, but the ability of the alliance and faction to coordinate, grow quickly, control territory and choose the right moment to fight.</p>
    <p>The season is a <b>4 vs 4 server war</b>. Success depends on early development, diplomacy with allies and battle management during the decisive weeks.</p>
    <p>The first weeks must not be played impulsively. Do not waste troops or speedups on low-value attacks. Build a solid base, increase seasonal resistance, produce dedicated resources, fish, donate to Faction Technology and prepare for the real war.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="goal" class="seasonSection">
    <h2>1. Main objective of S6</h2>
    <div class="seasonGrid seasonGrid2">
      <article class="seasonInfoCard featureCard"><div class="seasonIcon">🗺️</div><h3>Progressive control</h3><p>The map requires territory control: many captures must be connected to territory already owned. Cities, passes, bridges, outposts and strategic areas should be conquered through a continuous line.</p></article>
      <article class="seasonInfoCard featureCard"><div class="seasonIcon">⛩️</div><h3>Altar exception</h3><p>Altars do not require connected territory and have a special strategic role: they unlock alliance skills that can strongly affect battles.</p></article>
    </div>
    <ul class="seasonChecklist seasonPillList"><li>grow quickly during the first week;</li><li>keep discipline and avoid pointless PvP;</li><li>control key map points;</li><li>coordinate with allies;</li><li>save resources for the hardest weeks;</li><li>protect the Sanctuary and contest Altars.</li></ul>
  </section>

  <section id="week-one" class="seasonSection">
    <h2>2. First week priorities</h2>
    <div class="seasonGrid seasonGrid3">
      <article class="seasonInfoCard"><h3>Profession</h3><p>Choose <b>Engineer</b> immediately. Early Season 6 is about snowballing construction, resources and seasonal buildings. Warlord comes later for the main combat group.</p></article>
      <article class="seasonInfoCard"><h3>Season buildings</h3><p>Raise the <b>Mushroom Institute</b> to at least level 4, upgrade <b>Spore Factories</b> to level 10 one by one, and keep the <b>Protector Camp</b> at the highest available level.</p></article>
      <article class="seasonInfoCard"><h3>Daily activity</h3><p>Complete Chaos Elite at least for the daily first win, farm zombies, fish, donate and collect War Merits. Small players are useful when they do these actions consistently.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="calendar" class="seasonSection">
    <h2>3. Calendar and captures</h2>
    <ol class="seasonTimeline"><li><b>Day 1-2:</b> growth, buildings, resistance, profession setup and resource saving.</li><li><b>Day 3:</b> first level 1 cities can be captured if ordered.</li><li><b>Day 5:</b> level 2 cities become available.</li><li><b>Week 3:</b> neutral Altars begin to matter.</li><li><b>Around week 5:</b> the harder combat phase starts; only prepared players should switch to Warlord.</li><li><b>Final weeks:</b> faction coordination, Sanctuary defense and decisive 4v4 battles.</li></ol>
  </section>

  <section id="fishing" class="seasonSection">
    <h2>4. Fishing, donations and War Merits</h2>
    <p>Fishing is not a side activity. Fish donations strengthen Faction Technology, give merit to individual players and help the whole faction scale. Blessed Fish should be used for Mushroom Institute buffs when required, while legendary fish can be evaluated for the personal Index if their bonuses are useful.</p>
    <ul class="seasonChecklist"><li>fish every day in the available zones;</li><li>donate fish regularly to Faction Technology;</li><li>use War Merits without fear: spending them does not reduce already earned ranking points;</li><li>do not ignore support activities, because they decide faction growth.</li></ul>
  </section>

  <section id="diplomacy" class="seasonSection"><h2>5. Diplomacy and territory</h2><p>Season 6 is won through faction management. Follow R4/R5 instructions, respect agreements with allied servers, avoid unauthorized attacks and build connected territory lines. Bridges, passes and city links are strategic assets, not random targets.</p></section>

  <section id="war" class="seasonSection"><h2>6. War phase</h2><p>Do not rush into war during the first days. Save troops, speedups and healing for the weeks where the map actually decides the ranking. The combat core can move to Warlord near the hard phase, while everyone else should continue supporting growth, donations and rally filling.</p></section>

  <section id="altars" class="seasonSection"><h2>7. Altars: the strategic weapon</h2><p>Altars in the center are special objectives because they can unlock alliance abilities. They do not require connected territory, so they can become decisive even when map lines are blocked. Contest them only with coordinated orders.</p></section>

  <section id="routine" class="seasonSection"><h2>8. Daily routine</h2><ol class="seasonChecklist"><li>check alliance orders before attacking;</li><li>complete seasonal buildings and research priorities;</li><li>do Chaos Elite daily;</li><li>fish and donate;</li><li>farm War Merits;</li><li>join ordered captures and rallies;</li><li>save troops, healing and speedups for decisive weeks.</li></ol></section>

  <section id="errors" class="seasonSection"><h2>9. Mistakes to avoid</h2><ul class="seasonChecklist seasonDangerList"><li>choosing Warlord too early;</li><li>ignoring the Mushroom Institute;</li><li>not raising Spore Factories to level 10;</li><li>skipping daily Chaos Elite;</li><li>not fishing or donating;</li><li>wasting troops in pointless PvP;</li><li>attacking enemy cities without orders;</li><li>not coordinating with R4/R5.</li></ul><p class="seasonRule"><b>The season is won through consistency and discipline, not isolated attacks.</b></p></section>

  <section id="faq" class="seasonSection"><h2>FAQ — Season 6</h2><div class="seasonFaq"><details open><summary>What should I do first?</summary><p>Choose <b>Engineer</b>, start seasonal buildings and complete activities that give materials and War Merits.</p></details><details><summary>When should we switch to Warlord?</summary><p>Not immediately. It is recommended for the main combat group close to week 5.</p></details><details><summary>Why is fishing important?</summary><p>Fish support Faction Technology, strengthen everyone and give personal merits.</p></details><details><summary>What is our strategic role?</summary><p>Defend the ordered front, cooperate with allies, block passes and bridges, contest Altars and avoid wasting strength.</p></details></div></section>
</section>

